{
  "number": 345,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/345",
  "title": "Listing community widgets in the documentation",
  "body": "cc @Shipow @speedblue, I saw some documentation website screenshots where we have community widget documentation along with our widgets (using Author: @algolia etc..)\n\nI feel for a start and even in the future as for community widgets we could have a dedicated page accessible on the left navigation that will list the community widgets and their github.\n\nTrying to have community widgets mixed with official ones on the same page will be confusing: you'll have to maintain the documentation for things we do not maintain.\n\nThis would be like jquery website having community widget documentation on the main website: seems confusing for a developer I think.\n\nA simple page that we will create once we have community widgets should be enough for a start.\n\nWDYT?\n",
